Before doing anything, read these two files in full:

1. `CLAUDE.md` (repo root) — stack, repo structure, and coding conventions.
2. `docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md` — current phase progress, known gaps, and the
   next recommended tasks. This is the source of truth for what's done and
   what's next; don't re-derive it from guesswork.

Key rules from `CLAUDE.md`, restated here so they apply even if the file
above isn't picked up for some reason:

- Backend modules follow controller → service → repository (NestJS).
- DTOs are validated with `class-validator` + `class-transformer`.
- All Meta Graph/Marketing API calls go through the shared
  `MetaClientService` wrapper (`backend/src/meta-client/`) — never call
  `axios`/`fetch` against `graph.facebook.com` directly from anywhere else.
- Tests are required for services before moving on. Look at an existing
  `*.spec.ts` in the module you're touching for the mocking pattern already
  in use — don't invent a new one.
- Never commit `.env` or real credentials. `.env.example` stays blank.
- Don't run `eslint --fix` (or any formatter) repo-wide — scope it to the
  files you actually touched, or fix formatting by hand. Pre-existing
  formatting debt in a file you're editing is not yours to fix unless asked.

When you finish a session: update `docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md` — check off
finished tasks, add anything new you found under "Known gaps," and append a
line to "Session log" with the date and current commit hash so the next
session (yours or Claude Code's) knows where things stand.
